Care Of Kids During Season ChangeKeeping your babies safe during the season change is very
important as thats when they tend to get virals. Season change is my biggest nightmare always
however this time I am over cautious because of this Pandemic situation. This time my safeguard is
more as prevention is always better than cure.These are some tips :-1. Keep your child hydrated as it
helps in regulating the body temperature. So water or soup is best suggested and not juices. And yes
for infants below 6 months mothers milk is enough so dont give water to them.2. Intake of Vitamin C
and fibre is very important as it helps build immune system as it acts as a booster in our bodies. And
fibre helps in proper functioning of galt. Some vitamin C enriched fruits are lemon, orange, pineapple,
papaya, kiwi.You can also squeeze lemon in their meal when they are having dal rice. High fibre food
Keywords: healthybabyfoodideas healthylifestlye immunitybooster momlife mumbaimoms pandemic

journey but it was definitely more than that. It was also going to be about me.. about balancing &
finding myself & my motherhood. .I always had big dreams that I would often make presentations in

Statement: An ode to our Farmers and Harvest.Please appreciate the hard work and dedication of our farming
community. Respect the fresh produce in the market. Do not haggle and bargain while buying
vegetables and greens. Farmers do the hardest job on this planet and yet are underpaid and under
appreciated. So please do not take them for granted..How can you help?.1. Try to buy directly from
farmers or farmer markets as much as possible (Avoid Supermarkets).2. Eat Seasonal Produce
(Avoid Frozen & Canned Foods)..3. Find opportunities to Volunteer and help in farms..4. If there are
farmers around your place unaware of technology and best practices, help them with information and
awareness..5. Form a community in your neighbourhood and create a market for produce directly
bought from farmers. This avoids middlemen and monopolyand farmers get fair price...Do your bit,
small or big, to help our farmers. Its needed, right now...#lifeoutsidecubicle#bornoninstagram
There is no one definition for How to Travel?.Some have limited time & go hop hop places..Some
prefer slow travel & exploring a place with all its heart & soul..Some choose history & culture & some
opt for parties & hustle bustle..Some disconnect from technology & the world to spend time with
themselves in the middle of nature..Some prioritise volunteering and conservation..I choose different
things at different times and usually prefer homestays, spend time with locals, and bit of photography..
And this wonderful friend of mine @_.llb._ enjoys every second of his travel, observes everything
around, and makes sketches & notes..Travel is beyond beautiful and it presents us with unlimited
opportunities to become a better individual. :love_letter:..:question_mark: Whats your way of travel?...
